<section class="section" aria-labelledby="pid-title">
  <header class="section-header">
    <h2 class="section-title" id="pid-title">PID Integration (Days 28–30)</h2>
  </header>
  
  <article class="card">
    <h3>Resource</h3>
    <p><strong>Brian Douglas — "Control Systems Lectures" (PID Playlist)</strong></p>
    <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wkfEZmsQqiA&list=PLn8PRpmsu08pQBgjxYFXSsODEF3Jqmm-y" target="_blank" rel="noopener">youtube.com/playlist?list=PLn8PRpmsu08pQBgjxYFXSsODEF3Jqmm-y</a></p>
    <p>Watch: <em>PID Control Intro</em>, <em>PID Tuning</em>, <em>PID Implementation</em>. ~45 minutes total.</p>
  </article>
  
  <article class="card" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
    <h3>Why Intuition-First</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Equations-first teaches symbol manipulation. Intuition-first teaches <em>behavior prediction</em>.</li>
      <li>On a VEX robot: you feel overshoot, you see steady-state error, you hear oscillation. The equations map to those sensations.</li>
      <li>Brian Douglas builds mental models: "P is spring, I is accumulated memory, D is damper." That transfers to tuning.</li>
      <li>Day 29–30: you implement PID on a simulated plant (mass-spring-damper), then tune by feel. No Ziegler-Nichols memorization.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
  
  <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top: var(--space-5);">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Day 28 — P Controller</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Simulate 1D mass with force input</li>
        <li>Implement P-only: <code>u = Kp * error</code></li>
        <li>Observe: steady-state error, oscillation vs Kp</li>
        <li>Log: Kp values tested, resulting behavior</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Day 29 — PI Controller</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Add integral term: <code>integral += error * dt</code></li>
        <li>Anti-windup: clamp integral</li>
        <li>Observe: zero steady-state error, overshoot trade-off</li>
        <li>Log: Ki values, settling time, overshoot</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Day 30 — Full PID + Final Project</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Add derivative: <code>derivative = (error - prevError) / dt</code></li>
        <li>Noise handling: low-pass filter on D</li>
        <li>Tune all three gains by feel</li>
        <li>Integrate into Student Management System as "Grade PID Simulator" module (optional stretch)</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>VEX Transfer</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Drivetrain distance PID → position control</li>
        <li>Lift height PID → hold position against gravity</li>
        <li>Flywheel velocity PID → consistent RPM</li>
        <li>Same structure, different plants. The tuning mindset transfers.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>